rdware value, which can mean better LTV, longer tenor, or lower spread on your next cluster.\n\nWould a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? Happy to work around your schedule.\n\nJosh Augustine\nCorgi\ncorgi.xyz"}','cold_intro_operator','draft','2026-03-21 02:37:38',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO email_drafts VALUES('cf53a004-ac98-4645-8dcf-998dc22483d0','2b168fae-478d-4a86-b85c-5737cd77f1f8','GPU financing — a quick thought','{"html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: #1a1a1a; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }\n    p { margin: 0 0 16px; }\n    a { color: #2563eb; }\n    .signature { margin-top: 28px; color: #555; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p>Hi Joakim,</p>\n\n  <p>I''ll keep this short. Verda is building serious GPU infrastructure — European AI cloud operator (formerly DataCrunch). Raised $64M Series A including debt component. Focused on EU AI compute.. The financing piece is where we can help.</p>\n\n  <p>We help GPU operators get a better debt structure by reducing residual value risk on the hardware. A lot of lenders still get stuck on one question: what are the GPUs worth at maturity? We solve for that.</p>\n\n  <p>The short version: lenders get more comfort on future hardware value, which can mean better LTV, longer tenor, or lower spread on your next cluster.</p>\n\n  <p>Would a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? Happy to work around your schedule.</p>\n\n  <div class=\"signature\">\n    <p>Josh Augustine<br>\n    Corgi<br>\n    <a href=\"https://corgi.xyz\">corgi.xyz</a></p>\n  </div>\n\n  \n</body>\n</html>","text":"Hi Joakim,\n\nI''ll keep this short. Verda is building serious GPU infrastructure — European AI cloud operator (formerly DataCrunch). Raised $64M Series A including debt component. Focused on EU AI compute.. The financing piece is where we can help.\n\nWe help GPU operators get a better debt structure by reducing residual value risk on the hardware. A lot of lenders still get stuck on one question: what are the GPUs worth at maturity? We solve for that.\n\nThe short version: lenders get more comfort on future hardware value, which can mean better LTV, longer tenor, or lower spread on your next cluster.\n\nWould a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? Happy to work around your schedule.\n\nJosh Augustine\nCorgi\ncorgi.xyz"}','cold_intro_operator','draft','2026-03-21 02:37:38',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO email_drafts VALUES('1d1a3555-124e-4848-acee-dc5ee879393f','ccdc4b92-26fb-448d-8ccd-5dfde7149789','GPU-backed credit — the residual value question','{"html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: #1a1a1a; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }\n    p { margin: 0 0 16px; }\n    a { color: #2563eb; }\n    .signature { margin-top: 28px; color: #555; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p>Hi David,</p>\n\n  <p>Upper90 is active in AI infrastructure credit — Asset-backed private credit fund. Led the Crusoe Energy credit facility — a landmark GPU infrastructure financing deal.. The question we keep hearing from lenders is: what are the GPUs worth at maturity?</p>\n\n  <p>We help lenders make more GPU-backed loans by protecting downside on future collateral value. The deal economics look great until someone asks about end-of-term hardware value. We give you a cleaner answer.</p>\n\n  <p>It''s meant to make the deal easier to underwrite — a cleaner IC story, better recovery assumptions, more confidence to deploy. Not add complexity.</p>\n\n  <p>Would a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? We can show you how it fits the credit box.</p>\n\n  <div class=\"signature\">\n    <p>Josh Augustine<br>\n    Corgi<br>\n    <a href=\"https://corgi.xyz\">corgi.xyz</a></p>\n  </div>\n\n  \n</body>\n</html>","text":"Hi David,\n\nUpper90 is active in AI infrastructure credit — Asset-backed private credit fund. Led the Crusoe Energy credit facility — a landmark GPU infrastructure financing deal.. The question we keep hearing from lenders is: what are the GPUs worth at maturity?\n\nWe help lenders make more GPU-backed loans by protecting downside on future collateral value. The deal economics look great until someone asks about end-of-term hardware value. We give you a cleaner answer.\n\nIt''s meant to make the deal easier to underwrite — a cleaner IC story, better recovery assumptions, more confidence to deploy. Not add complexity.\n\nWould a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? We can show you how it fits the credit box.\n\nJosh Augustine\nCorgi\ncorgi.xyz"}','cold_intro_lender','draft','2026-03-21 02:40:08',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO email_drafts VALUES('504c6699-f5a2-48c4-a311-72df9dd26ad7','837ee315-f839-43e7-be5f-2ad693525c17','GPU-backed credit — the residual value question','{"html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: #1a1a1a; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }\n    p { margin: 0 0 16px; }\n    a { color: #2563eb; }\n    .signature { margin-top: 28px; color: #555; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p>Hi Richard,</p>\n\n  <p>Victory Park Capital is active in AI infrastructure credit — Asset-backed credit specialist with expertise in technology and infrastructure lending. Active in alternative asset finance.. The question we keep hearing from lenders is: what are the GPUs worth at maturity?</p>\n\n  <p>We help lenders make more GPU-backed loans by protecting downside on future collateral value. The deal economics look great until someone asks about end-of-term hardware value. We give you a cleaner answer.</p>\n\n  <p>It''s meant to make the deal easier to underwrite — a cleaner IC story, better recovery assumptions, more confidence to deploy. Not add complexity.</p>\n\n  <p>Would a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? We can show you how it fits the credit box.</p>\n\n  <div class=\"signature\">\n    <p>Josh Augustine<br>\n    Corgi<br>\n    <a href=\"https://corgi.xyz\">corgi.xyz</a></p>\n  </div>\n\n  \n</body>\n</html>","text":"Hi Richard,\n\nVictory Park Capital is active in AI infrastructure credit — Asset-backed credit specialist with expertise in technology and infrastructure lending. Active in alternative asset finance.. The question we keep hearing from lenders is: what are the GPUs worth at maturity?\n\nWe help lenders make more GPU-backed loans by protecting downside on future collateral value. The deal economics look great until someone asks about end-of-term hardware value. We give you a cleaner answer.\n\nIt''s meant to make the deal easier to underwrite — a cleaner IC story, better recovery assumptions, more confidence to deploy. Not add complexity.\n\nWould a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? We can show you how it fits the credit box.\n\nJosh Augustine\nCorgi\ncorgi.xyz"}','cold_intro_lender','draft','2026-03-21 02:40:08',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
